The letter {{AurB|sh}} was the thirty-third letter of the [[Aurebesh/Legends|Aurebesh]] alphabet. It was pronounced "shen", and had the value of /SH/.<ref name="Written Word">{{Hyperspace|url=hyperspace/source/writtenword/index.html?page=1|text=The Written Word|int=The Written Word}}</ref>

==Behind the scences==
Shen is meant to be a single letter used for the SH sound, like, for example, Š/Sz is used in some Slavic languages or Ш in the Cyrillic alphabet. The "besh" in "Aurebesh" is thus spelled besh-esk-shen, rather than besh-esk-senth-herf.

